{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3871", "repo": "rails", "body": "> One advantage of putting it in core is that IIRC there are things it can't quite pull off (values off joins, maybe?) without monkeypatching AR. Ernie?\r\n\r\nIn general, I think it's valuable for core to provide both a query engine (arel), a full ORM (AR), and a way to fetch lightweight values through the same query engine. These seem nicely complementary, and promoting Valium to a first-class citizen could well relieve  some of the reputation for GC memory pressure that Rails has accreted. ", "_id": {"$oid": "52383067bd3543c15100f643"}, "issue_id": 3871, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3062224", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3871#issuecomment-3062224", "updated_at": "2011-12-08T13:23:03Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaylevitt/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaylevitt/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaylevitt/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaylevitt/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaylevitt", "login": "jaylevitt", "gravatar_id": "b8aca816cb8646a855175f64bdfa2838", "html_url": "https://github.com/jaylevitt", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaylevitt/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaylevitt/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaylevitt/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/b8aca816cb8646a855175f64bdfa2838?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fc99e757a469e0631c1a61e97949885f1.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaylevitt/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 11246, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaylevitt/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-12-08T13:23:03Z", "id": 3062224, "owner": "rails"}
